      <bioghist id="ref7">
         <head>Biographical/Historical Sketch</head>
         <p>Stanford Against Conscription (SAC), formerly or also known as Students Against the Draft, was a campus group which existed from early 1979 until 1985. A coalition of Stanford groups and individuals concerned and active in opposition to the draft, SAC worked at many levels: campus, the Bay Area, statewide, and nationally. The organization attempted to operate non-heirarchically through the consensus process.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref8">
         <head>Summary</head>
         <p>Stanford Against Conscription (SAC), formerly or also known as Students Against the Draft, was a campus group which existed from early 1979 until 1985. A coalition of Stanford groups and individuals concerned and active in opposition to the draft, SAC worked at many levels: campus, the Bay Area, statewide, nationally and even internationally. 'Ihe organization attempted to operate non-heirarchically through the consensus process. 'Ihroughout SAC's histo:ry, its members made significant contributions to the cause of peace. 'Ihe collection contains records, articles, leaflets, momentos and reading material kept by the organization.</p>
      </scopecontent>
